# Node.js requires `nvm use 26`

This machine manages Node with **nvm**, and a bare shell does NOT have `node`/`npm`
on PATH. Before ANY Node.js command (`npm`, `npx`, `node`, `react-native`, `pod`
install that shells out to node, Metro, etc.), load nvm and select Node 26 in the
SAME shell invocation.

## Always prefix Node commands

```bash
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && nvm use 26 && <your command>
```

Examples:

```bash
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && nvm use 26 && npm install zustand
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && nvm use 26 && npm start
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && nvm use 26 && npx react-native run-ios --device
```

Symptom if you forget: `command not found: npm` (or `node`). Re-run with the
`source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && nvm use 26 &&` prefix.

The `abracadabra-rnapp` repo also ships a `StartMetro.command` wrapper that does
this for Metro specifically.
